G. M. MASTERS v. UNITED STATES of America. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 14, 1937. Maynard Tipps, of Nashville, Tenn., for appellant. Horace Frierson, Jr., of Nashville, Tenn., for the United States.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that this appeal be, and same is, dismissed without docketing, pursuant to motion of appellant. Costs to be charged as constructive earnings.

Appeal dismissed without docketing.
